FreeType crashes when it's in incremental mode and the font has a border.
It crashes when you try to dispose the FreeTypeBitmapFontData (which you should do according to the docs)
Some things to note:
It does NOT crash if I don't dispose the FreeTypeFontGenerator.
I does crash if I dispose the generator and the FreeTypeBitmapFontData.

The problem seems to be the disposing of the Stroker instance FreeType uses in incremental mode.

Reprocase: 

```

package com.badlogic.gdx.tests.lwjgl;

import com.badlogic.gdx.Gdx;
import com.badlogic.gdx.backends.lwjgl.LwjglApplication;
import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.Color;
import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.g2d.BitmapFont;
import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.g2d.freetype.*;
import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.g2d.freetype.FreeTypeFontGenerator.FreeTypeBitmapFontData;
import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.g2d.freetype.FreeTypeFontGenerator.FreeTypeFontParameter;
import com.badlogic.gdx.tests.utils.GdxTest;

public class CrashLauncher {

    public static void main (String... args) {
        new LwjglApplication(new FreeTypeCrashTest());
    }

    static class FreeTypeCrashTest extends GdxTest {

        BitmapFont font;
        FreeTypeFontGenerator generator;
        FreeTypeBitmapFontData data;

        public void create () {
            generator = new FreeTypeFontGenerator(Gdx.files.internal("data/arial.ttf"));

            FreeTypeFontParameter param = new FreeTypeFontParameter();
            param.incremental = true;
            param.borderWidth = 2f;
            param.characters = "H";

            data = new FreeTypeBitmapFontData();
            font = generator.generateFont(param, data);
        }

        @Override
        public void dispose () {
            generator.dispose();
            font.dispose();
            data.dispose();
        }
    }
}
```

